# Contributing Guide

First off, thank you for considering contributing ‚ù§Ô∏è
This project grows because of people like you.

---

## Ways to Contribute

You can contribute in many ways:

* Reporting bugs
* Suggesting features or improvements
* Improving documentation
* Submitting bug fixes
* Adding new features
* Reviewing pull requests

---

## Before You Start

Please make sure to:

1. Read the README.
2. Check existing issues to avoid duplicates.
3. Open an issue before starting large changes.

---

## Development Setup

### 1. Fork the Repository

Click **Fork** and clone your fork:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yash1648/github-final-project.git
cd <repo-name>
```

### 2. Create a Branch

Use a descriptive branch name:

```bash
git checkout -b feature/your-feature-name
```

Examples:

* `feature/add-authentication`
* `fix/login-bug`
* `docs/update-readme`

---

## Coding Guidelines

### General Principles

* Keep code simple and readable.
* Follow existing project structure and style.
* Write meaningful commit messages.
* Add comments where necessary.

### Commit Message Format

Use clear and descriptive messages:

```
type(scope): short description

Examples:
feat(auth): add JWT authentication
fix(api): handle null pointer exception
docs(readme): update setup instructions
```

Common commit types:

* `feat` ‚Üí new feature
* `fix` ‚Üí bug fix
* `docs` ‚Üí documentation
* `refactor` ‚Üí code refactoring
* `test` ‚Üí tests
* `chore` ‚Üí maintenance

---

## Pull Request Process

1. Ensure your branch is up to date:

   ```bash
   git pull origin main
   ```

2. Run tests and verify your changes.

3. Push your branch:

   ```bash
   git push origin feature/your-feature-name
   ```

4. Open a Pull Request and include:

   * Clear title and description
   * Screenshots (if UI changes)
   * Linked issue (if applicable)

---

## Pull Request Checklist

Before submitting, confirm:

* Code builds successfully
* No unnecessary files included
* Documentation updated if needed
* Changes are focused and minimal
* Tests added or updated (if applicable)

---

## Issue Guidelines

### Bug Report

Include:

* Steps to reproduce
* Expected behavior
* Actual behavior
* Environment details

### Feature Request

Include:

* Problem you want to solve
* Proposed solution
* Possible alternatives

---

## Code Review

All contributions will be reviewed by maintainers.
Feedback is part of the process‚Äîplease be patient and open to suggestions.

